header.gameNote: SUN BELT MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - QUARTERFINAL AT HOT SPRINGS AR

article.headline: Arkansas St. 64, Middle Tennessee 61
article.story: HOT SPRINGS, Ark. -- Trey Finn scored 16 points and Marcus Hooten scored 15, including two free throws in the final 9.5 seconds, and ninth seed Arkansas State stunned regular-season champion Middle Tennessee 64-61 in the Sun Belt tournament quarterfinals Sunday night. Brandon Peterson had 13 points and eight rebounds for the Red Wolves (14-19), the No. 9 seed who beat Florida Atlantic in the first round Saturday night. Arkansas State plays fifth-seeded North Texas in Monday night's semifinals. North Texas beat Louisiana-Lafayette 65-62. Raymond Cintron scored 15 points and LaRon Dendy 14 for Middle Tennessee (25-6). The Blue Raiders, 14-2 in the Sun Belt Conference season, trailed most of the second half at Summit Arena and missed five free throws in the final minute, including one by Dendy that would have tied it after his basket made it 60-59 with 12.9 seconds left. Middle Tennessee was 11 for 22 from the free-throw line.
